{
  "page": "Volantene fleet",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Tomasz_Jedruszek_Fleet_from_VolantisII.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/8/8d/Tomasz_Jedruszek_Fleet_from_VolantisII.JPG/350px-Tomasz_Jedruszek_Fleet_from_VolantisII.JPG\" width=\"350\" height=\"226\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/8/8d/Tomasz_Jedruszek_Fleet_from_VolantisII.JPG/525px-Tomasz_Jedruszek_Fleet_from_VolantisII.JPG 1.5x, /images/8/8d/Tomasz_Jedruszek_Fleet_from_VolantisII.JPG 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Tomasz_Jedruszek_Fleet_from_VolantisII.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Fleet from <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a>, by Tomasz Jedruszek © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>The <b>Volantene fleet</b> is the fleet of the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_City\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Free City\">Free City</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a>. While Volantis is powerful at sea,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> the city's greatest might is on land.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_volantis.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_volantis.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Three <a href=\"/index.php/Triarchs_of_Volantis\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Triarchs of Volantis\">triarchs</a> are elected annually to command the fleets and armies of Volantis.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_volantis.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_volantis.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Often green in color,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Volantene galleys are rowed by <a href=\"/index.php/Slaves\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Slaves\">slaves</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Volantene_fleet&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>At the start of the <a href=\"/index.php/Century_of_Blood\" title=\"Century of Blood\">Century of Blood</a>, Volantene fleets and armies gained control of <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Myr\" title=\"Myr\">Myr</a>, and the southern reaches of the <a href=\"/index.php/Rhoyne\" title=\"Rhoyne\">Rhoyne</a>. The imperialist <a href=\"/index.php/Tigers_(Volantis)\" title=\"Tigers (Volantis)\">tigers</a> overreached by attacking <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrosh\" title=\"Tyrosh\">Tyrosh</a>, however, and Volantis was pushed back by a coalition of <a href=\"/index.php/Free_Cities\" title=\"Free Cities\">Free Cities</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westerosi</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen\">Aegon Targaryen</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Dragonstone\" title=\"Lord of Dragonstone\">Lord of Dragonstone</a>, burned a Volantene fleet preparing to recapture Lys with the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonflame\" title=\"Dragonflame\">dragonflame</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Balerion\" title=\"Balerion\">Balerion the Black Dread</a>, and fire galleys from <a href=\"/index.php/Qohor\" title=\"Qohor\">Qohor</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Norvos\" title=\"Norvos\">Norvos</a> destroyed much of a Volantene fleet at <a href=\"/index.php/Dagger_Lake\" title=\"Dagger Lake\">Dagger Lake</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_doom_of_valyria.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_doom_of_valyria.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> A Volantene fleet also attempted to reclaim the <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_peninsula\" title=\"Valyrian peninsula\">Valyrian peninsula</a>, but it vanished in the <a href=\"/index.php/Smoking_Sea\" title=\"Smoking Sea\">Smoking Sea</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_doom_of_valyria.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_doom_of_valyria.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Triarch <a href=\"/index.php/Marqelo_Tagaros\" title=\"Marqelo Tagaros\">Marqelo Tagaros</a> dispatched a squadron of ships toward <a href=\"/index.php/Valyria\" title=\"Valyria\">Valyria</a> to search for the golden fleet of <a href=\"/index.php/Tommen_II_Lannister\" title=\"Tommen II Lannister\">Tommen II Lannister</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/King_of_the_Rock\" title=\"King of the Rock\">King of the Rock</a>, but the Volantenes returned having found no trace of the missing <a href=\"/index.php/Westermen\" title=\"Westermen\">westermen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Triarchs_of_Volantis\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Triarchs of Volantis\">triarchs of Volantis</a> have sent fleets to clear out <a href=\"/index.php/Pirate\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pirate\">pirate</a> dens from the <a href=\"/index.php/Stepstones\" title=\"Stepstones\">Stepstones</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_the_quarrelsome_daughters:_myr.2C_lys.2C_and_tyrosh.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_the_quarrelsome_daughters:_myr.2C_lys.2C_and_tyrosh.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> and corsairs from the <a href=\"/index.php/Basilisk_Isles\" title=\"Basilisk Isles\">Basilisk Isles</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafbeyond_the_free_cities:_the_basilisk_isles.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafbeyond_the_free_cities:_the_basilisk_isles.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Volantene_fleet&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Volantene_fleet&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Amid the <a href=\"/index.php/Targaryen_campaign_in_Slaver%27s_Bay\" title=\"Targaryen campaign in Slaver&#39;s Bay\">Targaryen campaign in Slaver's Bay</a>, envoys from <a href=\"/index.php/Yunkai\" title=\"Yunkai\">Yunkai</a> travel to <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a> to hire swords against <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Queen_of_Meereen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Queen of Meereen\">Queen of Meereen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> learns that Volantis is preparing for war against the dragon queen.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd18.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Quentyn_Martell\" title=\"Quentyn Martell\">Quentyn Martell</a> sees the harbor of Volantis crowded with warships, trading ships, and foreign vessels.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When the <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Company\" title=\"Golden Company\">Golden Company</a> nears Volantis, <a href=\"/index.php/Lysono_Maar\" title=\"Lysono Maar\">Lysono Maar</a> sneaks into the city and sees teeming with galleys, cogs, and carracks. Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">Jon Connington</a> believes the <a href=\"/index.php/Triarchs_of_Volantis\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Triarchs of Volantis\">triarchs of Volantis</a> would be willing to help transport the <a href=\"/index.php/Sellswords\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sellswords\">sellswords</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a> to remove them from their city's vicinity.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> A great Volantene fleet stops at <a href=\"/index.php/Lys\" title=\"Lys\">Lys</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup> while transporting the mercenaries to the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a>, but the <a href=\"/index.php/Landing_of_the_Golden_Company\" title=\"Landing of the Golden Company\">landing of the Golden Company</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Stormlands\" title=\"Stormlands\">stormlands</a> is disrupted by storms in the <a href=\"/index.php/Narrow_sea\" title=\"Narrow sea\">narrow sea</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd61.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lord Captain <a href=\"/index.php/Victarion_Greyjoy\" title=\"Victarion Greyjoy\">Victarion Greyjoy</a> leads the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Fleet\" title=\"Iron Fleet\">Iron Fleet</a> toward <a href=\"/index.php/Slaver%27s_Bay\" title=\"Slaver&#39;s Bay\">Slaver's Bay</a> to find Daenerys. When the <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a> briefly stop in Volantis for food and water, Victarion sees numerous Volantene galleys taking on provisions. The Volantenes have at least three hundred ships and possibly up to five hundred, including large dromonds of war. Victarion wants his smaller fleet to take Daenerys from <a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereen</a> before the Volantenes reach Slaver's Bay.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Daenerys disappears from <a href=\"/index.php/Daznak%27s_Pit\" title=\"Daznak&#39;s Pit\">Daznak's Pit</a> on the back of <a href=\"/index.php/Drogon\" title=\"Drogon\">Drogon</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd52.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd52.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> According to <a href=\"/index.php/Skahaz_mo_Kandaq\" title=\"Skahaz mo Kandaq\">Skahaz mo Kandaq</a>, Daenerys's new husband, King <a href=\"/index.php/Hizdahr_zo_Loraq\" title=\"Hizdahr zo Loraq\">Hizdahr zo Loraq</a>, is conspiring with the <a href=\"/index.php/Wise_Masters\" title=\"Wise Masters\">Wise Masters</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Yunkai\" title=\"Yunkai\">Yunkai</a>. The plotters want to kill <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaegal\" title=\"Rhaegal\">Rhaegal</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Viserion\" title=\"Viserion\">Viserion</a> before the Volantene fleet arrives,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd67.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup> and they would then open the gates of Meereen to the Volantene soldiers.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Volantene_fleet&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Pentos\" title=\"Pentos\">Pentos</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a> are all coastal cities blessed with great harbors. Trade is their life's blood, and their ships travel to the far ends of <a href=\"/index.php/Known_world\" title=\"Known world\">the earth</a>, from <a href=\"/index.php/Yi_Ti\" title=\"Yi Ti\">Yi Ti</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Leng\" title=\"Leng\">Leng</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Asshai\" title=\"Asshai\">Asshai-by-the-Shadow</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/Far_east\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Far east\">far east</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Lannisport\" title=\"Lannisport\">Lannisport</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Oldtown\" title=\"Oldtown\">Oldtown</a> on <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_the_quarrelsome_daughters:_myr.2C_lys.2C_and_tyrosh.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_the_quarrelsome_daughters:_myr.2C_lys.2C_and_tyrosh.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Yandel\" title=\"Yandel\">Yandel</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Harry</b>: We came to raise up <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(Young_Griff)\" title=\"Aegon Targaryen (Young Griff)\">a king</a> and queen who would lead us home to <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>, but <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">this Targaryen girl</a> seems more intent on planting olive trees than in reclaiming <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">her father's throne</a>. Meanwhile, her foes gather. <a href=\"/index.php/Yunkai\" title=\"Yunkai\">Yunkai</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/New_Ghis\" title=\"New Ghis\">New Ghis</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Tolos\" title=\"Tolos\">Tolos</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/Bloodbeard\" title=\"Bloodbeard\">Bloodbeard</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Tattered_Prince\" title=\"Tattered Prince\">Tattered Prince</a> will both be in the field against her ... and soon enough the fleets of <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Old Volantis</a> will descend on her as well. What does she have? Bedslaves with sticks?<br />\n<b>Jon</b>: <a href=\"/index.php/Unsullied\" title=\"Unsullied\">Unsullied</a>. And <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragons</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Harry_Strickland\" title=\"Harry Strickland\">Harry Strickland</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Connington\" title=\"Jon Connington\">Jon Connington</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Skahaz</b>: <a href=\"/index.php/Daznak%27s_Pit\" title=\"Daznak&#39;s Pit\">The pit</a> changed all. <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys</a> gone, <a href=\"/index.php/Yurkhaz_zo_Yunzak\" title=\"Yurkhaz zo Yunzak\">Yurkhaz</a> dead. In place of one old lion, a pack of jackals. <a href=\"/index.php/Bloodbeard\" title=\"Bloodbeard\">Bloodbeard</a> ... that one has no taste for peace. And there is more. Worse. <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a> has launched its fleet against us.<br />\n</p><p><b>Barristan</b>: Volantis. You are certain?<br />\n</p>\n<b>Skahaz</b>: Certain. The <a href=\"/index.php/Wise_Masters\" title=\"Wise Masters\">Wise Masters</a> know. So do their friends. The <a href=\"/index.php/Harpy\" title=\"Harpy\">Harpy</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Reznak_mo_Reznak\" title=\"Reznak mo Reznak\">Reznak</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Hizdahr_zo_Loraq\" title=\"Hizdahr zo Loraq\">Hizdahr</a>. This king will open the city gates to the Volantenes when they arrive.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Skahaz_mo_Kandaq\" title=\"Skahaz mo Kandaq\">Skahaz mo Kandaq</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Barristan_Selmy\" title=\"Barristan Selmy\">Barristan Selmy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>The storms would have scattered and delayed the Volantenes, even as they had <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Fleet\" title=\"Iron Fleet\">his own ships</a>. If fortune smiled, many of their warships might have sunk or run aground. But not all. No god was that good, and those green galleys that survived by now could well have sailed around <a href=\"/index.php/Valyria\" title=\"Valyria\">Valyria</a>. They will be sweeping north toward <a href=\"/index.php/Meereen\" title=\"Meereen\">Meereen</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Yunkai\" title=\"Yunkai\">Yunkai</a>, great dromonds of war teeming with <a href=\"/index.php/Slave\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Slave\">slave</a> soldiers. If the <a href=\"/index.php/Storm_God\" title=\"Storm God\">Storm God</a> spared them, by now they could be in the <a href=\"/index.php/Gulf_of_Grief\" title=\"Gulf of Grief\">Gulf of Grief</a>. Three hundred ships, perhaps as many as five hundred.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Victarion_Greyjoy\" title=\"Victarion Greyjoy\">Victarion Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Volantene_fleet&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_56\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 56\">Chapter 56</a>, The Iron Suitor.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_volantis.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_volantis.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">2.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_volantis.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\">2.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Free Cities: Volantis.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_34\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 34\">Chapter 34</a>, Cat Of The Canals.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">4.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Radwd22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\">4.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons-Chapter_22\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons-Chapter 22\">Chapter 22</a>, Tyrion VI.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_doom_of_valyria.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_doom_of_valyria.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\">5.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_doom_of_valyria.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\">5.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, Ancient History: The Doom of Valyria.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_westerlands.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Westerlands.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_the_quarrelsome_daughters:_myr.2C_lys.2C_and_tyrosh.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_the_quarrelsome_daughters:_myr.2C_lys.2C_and_tyrosh.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\">7.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_the_quarrelsome_daughters:_myr.2C_lys.2C_and_tyrosh.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\">7.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Free Cities: The Quarrelsome Daughters: Myr, Lys, and Tyrosh.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafbeyond_the_free_cities:_the_basilisk_isles.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafbeyond_the_free_cities:_the_basilisk_isles.7B.7B.